Commentary: Asitha with two slips and a gully, begins from over the stumps and bowls right on the money! Not a visible movement, on a good length, outside off, Ben Duckett gets in line of the ball and eases it with a solid front foot defence to short cover.
Default_Commentary: 0.1: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: With a perfect seam position, and a bit of an inward movement, Asitha bowls it on the middle, full in length, Ben Duckett prods ahead and firmly pushes it back to the bowler.
Default_Commentary: 0.2: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Play and a miss! Outside off on a hard length, Ben Duckett does not move his feet and tries to slash it hard but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 0.3: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Good-length delivery a shade outside off, Duckett goes for the square cut but plays it much closer to the body, and gets cramped for room as he mistimes it in front of covers.
Default_Commentary: 0.4: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: A streaky way to get underway! On the middle, curving in a shade on a fuller length, Ben Duckett closes the bat's face way early on the flick shot and gets a leading edge to the cover-point region for a quick single.
Default_Commentary: 0.5: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: Back of a length and on middle, at 129 kph, Dan Lawrence defends it to mid-wicket.
Default_Commentary: 0.6: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Vishwa Fernando begins with a couple of slips in place and a gully in position. Hits the deck hard outside off from over the pegs, Ben Duckett punches it off the back foot to the short cover region.
Default_Commentary: 1.1: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: This one tails in a long way, starts from the middle stump and goes down the leg side on a fullish length. Ben Duckett misses to flick it away and the keeper collects it by bending to his left.
Default_Commentary: 1.2: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Fuller and on the fifth stump line, Ben Duckett meets the ball underneath his eyes and defends it solidly on the front foot.
Default_Commentary: 1.3: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Over the top of off, on a length, and shaping inwards. Ben Duckett waits for it to arrive and tucks it with soft hands to wide mid-wicket and jogs for a single.
Default_Commentary: 1.4: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: Aims the middle and leg stump line with an inward movement, Dan Lawrence stands upright and glances it straight to square leg who misfields and parries the ball to mid-wicket, but is quick to redeem himself.
Default_Commentary: 1.5: Vishwa Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: There's that questioning line and length! Lands it on the leg stump line and moves it away from the batter around off, on a length, Dan Lawrence attempts for a firm push, but plays inside the line of the ball and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 1.6: Vishwa Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Swing and a miss! Full and across off, Ben Duckett has to really reach out for it as he extends his arms and slashes hard. Ends up getting beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 2.1: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length, fractionally swinging in from middle with the angle, Ben Duckett glances it with soft hands towards square leg.
Default_Commentary: 2.2: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Almost chopped on, but gets away with it does Duckett! A little bit slower in pace and outside off with a wobble seam, on a length, Ben Duckett goes back and across to cut it square but inside edges it past the pegs for a boundary at deep fine. That was close though.
Default_Commentary: 2.3: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, Four!

Commentary: Fuller and around the middle and off, Ben Duckett pushes it firmly to mid on.
Default_Commentary: 2.4: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Asitha hurls this one on a questioning length! Entices the batter to poke at it by bowling it full and in the channel of uncertainty, just outside off. Ben Duckett has a feel for it and prods forward to defend it. Plays it inside the line and gets beaten on the outside edge by a whisker.
Default_Commentary: 2.5: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Good-length delivery sliding down leg, Duckett lets it pass.
Default_Commentary: 2.6: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: WIDE! Sprays it well across and outside the tramline on a length. Wide given.
Default_Commentary: 3.1: Vishwa Fernando to Dan Lawrence, Wide!

Commentary: Corrects his length and line, on the middle and on the good length, Dan Lawrence gets behind the line of the ball and punches it solidly underneath his bat off the back foot.
Default_Commentary: 3.1: Vishwa Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: And again! Vishwa Fernando creates that angle across off on a good length, slightly leaving the batter with the movement. Dan Lawrence goes for the back foot punch to the off side but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 3.2: Vishwa Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Almost an identical line and length, outside off, Dan Lawrence shoulders arms at this one.
Default_Commentary: 3.3: Vishwa Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Oopsie! That took off quite late! Length ball across off, it skids and bounces more off the deck. Dan Lawrence offers no shot at it and the ball carries to the keeper where Dinesh Chandimal fails to read the excessive bounce and parries the ball behind the slips. The batters cross for a bye.
Default_Commentary: 3.4: Vishwa Fernando to Dan Lawrence, Bye.

Commentary: FOUR! Nice shot! Vishwa Fernando misses his line and bowls it full and down leg, Ben Duckett simply flicks it through the mid-wicket and mid on gap for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 3.5: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, Four!

Commentary: Similar length, but a bit closer to the body, Ben Duckett hits it across and threads the flick through mid-wicket and mid on. Kamindu Mendis chases the ball from the mid on region and does well to intercept it before the ropes with a slide. He lobs the ball to the converging fielder from mid-wicket and the throw comes in towards the bowler's end. Three taken in the meantime.
Default_Commentary: 3.6: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, 3 runs.

Commentary: Good length, across off, Ben Duckett pokes at it, looking for a back foot push but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 4.1: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Hard length at 134 kph, outside off, Ben Duckett weighs on the back foot and mistimes the pull shot along the ground to mid-wicket.
Default_Commentary: 4.2: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Shorter in length and well outside off, Ben Duckett cuts it past backward point. Kamindu runs after it and puts in a slide near the ropes to pull it back. He executes it well and saves one for his team.
Default_Commentary: 4.3: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, 3 runs.

Commentary: Hard-length delivery outside off, Dan Lawrence lets it go.
Default_Commentary: 4.4: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: At 129 kph, good length, outside off, Dan Lawrence leaves it alone. The ball carries to the keeper with a bit of a lateral movement, but Chandimal manages to collect it well and sharply behind the wickets.
Default_Commentary: 4.5: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Asitha hurls this one on a fuller length, around off, Dan Lawrence gets on the front foot and pushes it firmly to mid off.
Default_Commentary: 4.6: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Lahiru Kumar starts with a couple of slips in place. Starts a bit wayward on the hard length, nipping in and going down leg. Ben Duckett misses to pull as the ball sneaks through under his gloves. Dinesh Chandimal moves to his right as the ball moves away very late behind the wickets. Does manage to get his right hand at it but the ball deflects off his gloves towards the short fine region. The batters cross. Chandimal is struggling with his right hand, the same hand on which he took a very heavy blow while batting in the second Test.
Default_Commentary: 5.1: Lahiru Kumara to Ben Duckett, 2 Byes.

Commentary: Lahiru Kumar bowls full and around off, Ben Duckett pushes it towards mid off on the front foot.
Default_Commentary: 5.2: Lahiru Kumara to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Now that's a gracious shot! Kumara lands it on the back of a length, outside off, Ben Duckett weighs on the back foot, sees the width and cashes on it with a late square cut. Manages to pierce the cover-point gap for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 5.3: Lahiru Kumara to Ben Duckett, Four!

Commentary: Full on the off stump, Ben Duckett taps it towards cover for a quick single.
Default_Commentary: 5.4: Lahiru Kumara to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: First runs for Lawrence and he gets a huge cheer from the spectators at the Oval. Over the top of the middle, on the back of a length, Dan Lawrence tucks it off the back foot towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Default_Commentary: 5.5: Lahiru Kumara to Dan Lawrence, 2 runs.

Commentary: Good leave! Kumara lands it on a nagging length, slightly nipping back in after pitching outside off, Dan Lawrence watches the ball closely and opts out as he hangs his bat in the air.
Default_Commentary: 5.6: Lahiru Kumara to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Keeps it straight, keeps it full, shapes in a touch, Ben Duckett stays in his crease and blocks it out with a straight bat down the pitch.
Default_Commentary: 6.1: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Goes fuller again but on the pads this time, Ben Duckett flicks it away nicely but finds short mid-wicket. That was there to be put away.
Default_Commentary: 6.2: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Asitha Fernando lands this one back of a length, on off, holds its line and skids through as well, Ben Duckett gets a bit hurried but manages well to pat it down to the off side.
Default_Commentary: 6.3: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Short of a length and around leg, Ben Duckett easily tucks it off his hips towards fine leg for a single.
Default_Commentary: 6.4: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: Hits the length hard, on the sixth stump line, this one takes off a bit after hitting the deck, Dan Lawrence watches it through, lifts it his bat and lets it go to the keeper.
Default_Commentary: 6.5: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Too straight again! On a length and angles into the leg side, Dan Lawrence nudges it away towards fine leg for a run.
Default_Commentary: 6.6: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, 1 run.

Commentary: Back of a length and around off, Dan Lawrence hops up a bit and dabs it down towards point.
Default_Commentary: 7.1: Lahiru Kumara to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Good-length delivery, shapes in sharply with a bit of an extra bounce, Dan Lawrence gets into an awkward position but flicks it away through mid-wicket for a single.
Default_Commentary: 7.2: Lahiru Kumara to Dan Lawrence, 1 run.

Commentary: Tocuh fuller, on middle, Ben Duckett tucks it away with soft hands towards the vacant mid-wicket region and comes back for the second run comfortably. Sri Lanka needs to stop giving away easy runs here.
Default_Commentary: 7.3: Lahiru Kumara to Ben Duckett, 2 runs.

Commentary: On a length and on middle, Ben Duckett works it wide of mid-wicket for another run.
Default_Commentary: 7.4: Lahiru Kumara to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: Goes very full this time, on off, shapes in a bit, Dan Lawrence steps across and drills it down the pitch, Lahiru Kumara does well on his follow-through to stop it.
Default_Commentary: 7.5: Lahiru Kumara to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length and on off, straightens after hitting the deck, Dan Lawrence plays it late and steers it towards point.
Default_Commentary: 7.6: Lahiru Kumara to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Nicely played! Milan Rathnayake starts with a cross-seam delivery, full and on off, Ben Duckett presents the full face of his bat and drives it smoothly past mid off, Dhananjaya de Silva from mid on chases after it, puts in a dive forward to push it back inside. Three runs taken.
Default_Commentary: 8.1: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, 3 runs.

Commentary: On a length and on middle, Dan Lawrence nudges it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Default_Commentary: 8.2: Milan Rathnayake to Dan Lawrence, 1 run.

Commentary: Pitches it up now, on middle and leg, no real movement on this one, Ben Duckett knocks it down to mid on.
Default_Commentary: 8.3: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Pulls his length back this time, on off, Ben Duckett takes a couple of steps forward and blocks it out to the off side.
Default_Commentary: 8.4: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Thrashed away! Milan Rathnayake goes fuller and just outside off, Ben Duckett comes down the track again, extends his arms and blasts it away over extra covers for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 8.5: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, Four!

Commentary: FOUR MORE! Good aggression from Ben Duckett! Overpitched and around off, Ben Duckett takes it on again, gets under it and lofts it beautifully over mid off for another boundary.
Default_Commentary: 8.6: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, Four!

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Dan Lawrence drills it down the pitch.
Default_Commentary: 9.1: Lahiru Kumara to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR....GONE! Lahiru Kumara draws first blood here! Dan Lawrence's lean patch continues as he goes back for yet another low score in this series. This one is banged hard into the pitch and around off, Dan Lawrence steps across and looks to flick it away, but does not fully commit his shot. He closes his bat face early as well and also takes his eyes off the ball. Ends up getting a leading edge and the ball goes straight up in the air, Pathum Nissanka at gully moves forward and takes a simple catch. Lawrence looked vulnerable in dealing with the deliveries outside off and was constantly trying to drag those to the leg side. He perishes on 5 (21). England are 45/1.
Default_Commentary: 9.2: Lahiru Kumara to Dan Lawrence, OUT! c Pathum Nissanka b Lahiru Kumara.
Howout: c Pathum Nissanka b Lahiru Kumara

Commentary: Back of a length and angles in, Ollie Pope tries to hook it away but misses as the ball goes off his pads towards fine leg. A leg bye is taken.
Default_Commentary: 9.3: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, Leg bye.

Commentary: Fuller this time, on the pads, Ben Duckett clips it away wide of deep square leg for a brace.
Default_Commentary: 9.4: Lahiru Kumara to Ben Duckett, 2 runs.

Commentary: On a length and on leg, Ben Duckett works it around the corner for another run.
Default_Commentary: 9.5: Lahiru Kumara to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: Hard length and on off, shapes in, Ollie Pope leaves it alone, Dinesh Chandimal dives to stop it but only manages to parry it away allowing a bye. He is having a torrid time behind the stumps here.
Default_Commentary: 9.6: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, Bye.

Commentary: FOUR! Lovely shot! Milan Rathnayake lands this back of a length and outside off, Ollie Pope accepts the width on offer, waits for it and cuts it away almost from behind the stumps, it zips past backward point and races away for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 10.1: Milan Rathnayake to Ollie Pope, Four!

Commentary: Pitched up and on off, Ollie Pope looks to drive but losses his bottom hand, fails to get the timing as the ball rolls towards mid off.
Default_Commentary: 10.2: Milan Rathnayake to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Fuller in length and on off again, Ollie Pope this time prods forward and blocks it out.
Default_Commentary: 10.3: Milan Rathnayake to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Hits the length hard and in that channel outside off, shapes away a touch, Ollie Pope offers no shot at it.
Default_Commentary: 10.4: Milan Rathnayake to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Short of a length and outside off, shapes away again, Ollie Pope goes after it and slashes hard but fails to connect.
Default_Commentary: 10.5: Milan Rathnayake to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Hard length and around off, Ollie Pope punches it towards deep point for a single.
Default_Commentary: 10.6: Milan Rathnayake to Ollie Pope, 1 run.

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Ollie Pope gets forward and plays a front foot defense towards short covers.
Default_Commentary: 11.1: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: On a length and around off, Ollie Pope looks to guide it away but ends up stabbing it towards short covers again.
Default_Commentary: 11.2: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Lahiru Kumara serves this full and on the sixth stump line, Ollie Pope steps across and drives it away with his bottom hand coming through, it goes past mid off but the fielder does well to chase after it and stop it. Three more added to the the total.
Default_Commentary: 11.3: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, 3 runs.

Commentary: Short of a length and on off, Ben Duckett stays back and looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his boots as the ball goes nowhere.
Default_Commentary: 11.4: Lahiru Kumara to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length and around off, Ben Duckett steers it away nicely wide of point, Dimuth Karunaratne at cover-point dives to his right to make a fine stop. He certainly saves a boundary there, the batters cross for one.
Default_Commentary: 11.5: Lahiru Kumara to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: SIX! That's big! Lahiru Kumara tries to test the batter with a short ball, but this one sits up nicely and is around leg as well, Ollie Pope picks it up nicely and hooks it over the deep square leg fence for the first biggie of this Test.
Default_Commentary: 11.6: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, Six!

Commentary: FOUR! Not from the middle of the bat, but it will work for Ben Duckett! Milan Rathnayake comes from over the wicket and bowls on a length outside off. Ben Duckett extends his arms and guides it from the outer part of his willow through backward point and gets a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 12.1: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, Four!

Commentary: Short of a length and angling on off. Ben Duckett hangs back and blocks it down to the pitch.
Default_Commentary: 12.2: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! TOP SHOT! Back of a length and just outside off, around fifth stump. Ben Duckett rocks back and punches it hard towards the gap in the cover region to get another boundary in the over.
Default_Commentary: 12.3: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, Four!

Commentary: On a length outside off. Ben Duckett taps it towards cover-point and calls for a run but Ollie Pope instantly shouts 'No' and denies the single. It's a thumbs-up from Duckett.
Default_Commentary: 12.4: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Short of a length on off. Ben Duckett prods and defends it down.
Default_Commentary: 12.5: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Fuller on the off. Ben Duckett lunges and looks to defend but gets beaten on the outer edge.
Default_Commentary: 12.6: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Full-length delivery just outside off. Ollie Pope leans towards the delivery and drives it gently towards mid off.
Default_Commentary: 13.1: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Fullish and wide outside off. Ollie Pope looks to drill it hard but gets beaten on the outer edge.
Default_Commentary: 13.2: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Pitched up, and outside off. Ollie Pope solidly defends to his front.
Default_Commentary: 13.3: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Sprays fuller, just outside off, angling towards the stump. Ollie Pope plants his front foot and blocks it right under his eyesight.
Default_Commentary: 13.4: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Full-length delivery just outside off. Ollie Pope camps back and eases it towards the off side.
Default_Commentary: 13.5: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Pitches it up, on off. Ollie Pope rests it down towards the cover region for no runs.
Default_Commentary: 13.6: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Vishwa Fernando comes from over the wicket and sprays it fuller, on off, shaping it in. Ben Duckett eases it down to the pitch.
Default_Commentary: 14.1: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Pitched up, once again just outside off. Ben Duckett comes forward and pushes it towards cover region for no runs.
Default_Commentary: 14.2: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: FIFTY FOR BEN DUCKETT! Fernando bowls on a good length outside off. Ben Duckett trusts the width of the delivery and hangs back to smash it through the cover region. The fielder patrolling the region tries to mop it up but it bursts through his hands and parries away behind in the deep. The batters take three runs in the middle and Duckett gets his tenth half-century in this format of cricket.
Default_Commentary: 14.3: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, 3 runs.

Commentary: Short of a length outside off. Ollie Pope looks to cut but misses the hit.
Default_Commentary: 14.4: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length outside off. Ollie Pope punches it towards mid off.
Default_Commentary: 14.5: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Another bouncer on middle and leg. Ollie Pope shuffles across the stumps and looks to clip it but misses and gets thumped on his thigh pad. The ball rolls towards his off side. Pope wants to take a single but rightfully sent back by Duckett as Fernando is quick to charge towards the ball and has a shy at the batter's end as well.
Default_Commentary: 14.6: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Asitha Fernando comes over the wicket and bowls on a good length on middle. Ben Duckett bunts it towards backward square leg region and gets a single.
Default_Commentary: 15.1: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: Much fuller, wide outside off, swinging it away from the batter. Ollie Pope prods, extends his arms and drives it through the gap of mid off and extra-cover, towards the sweeper cover region. The batters take three.
Default_Commentary: 15.2: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, 3 runs.

Commentary: On a length on off. Ben Duckett eases it towards the front of the gully fielder for no runs.
Default_Commentary: 15.3: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Good-length delivery on middle and off. Ben Duckett camps back and blocks it from the inner part of his willow towards the square leg region.
Default_Commentary: 15.4: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Tad fuller, but sprays down the leg. Ben Duckett looks to flick it but misses on the inner edge.
Default_Commentary: 15.5: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Hard-length delivery on off, shaping it in. Ben Duckett dabs it towards mid on.
Default_Commentary: 15.6: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! EXQUISITE! Vishwa Fernando comes from 'over the wicket and bowls it outside off, angling it away from the right-hander. Ollie Pope reaches it and cuts it hard through the backward point region and gets another boundary added to his account.
Default_Commentary: 16.1: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, Four!

Commentary: Fuller and down the leg. Ollie Pope tries to flick it but misses.
Default_Commentary: 16.2: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Good-length delivery, angling outside off. Ollie Pope looks to play at it but gets beaten on the outer edge.
Default_Commentary: 16.3: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Hard length, down the leg side. Ollie Pope hops a bit to tuck it towards fine leg but misses once again.
Default_Commentary: 16.4: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Fuller on off. Ollie Pope presses forward and blocks it out.
Default_Commentary: 16.5: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length, on middle and leg. Ollie Pope clips it towards deep square leg and gets a single.
Default_Commentary: 16.6: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, 1 run.

Commentary: Length delivery, wide outside off and nipping it away from the batter. Ollie Pope offers nothing to it. Dinesh Chandimal dives hard to his right and keeps it well.
Default_Commentary: 17.1: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Good-length delivery on off. Ollie Pope eases it towards mid on.
Default_Commentary: 17.2: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Hard-length delivery outside off, around seventh stump. Ollie Pope cuts this one towards deep point and gets a comfortable single.
Default_Commentary: 17.3: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, 1 run.

Commentary: Fuller and pitching down the leg side, nipping into the batter. Ben Duckett goes for a flick but misses to connect.
Default_Commentary: 17.4: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Fuller on leg. Ben Duckett clips it towards the gap of deep square leg and deep fine leg. A couple taken in between.
Default_Commentary: 17.5: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, 2 runs.

Commentary: Full and on the pad. Ben Duckett flicks it towards deep backward square leg and gets nothing single.
Default_Commentary: 17.6: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: Good-length delivery on off. Ben Duckett blocks it a bit late and the ball drops dead on the pitch.
Default_Commentary: 18.1: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Fullish and wide outside of. Ben Duckett looks to lash it out but misses on the outer edge.
Default_Commentary: 18.2: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: On a length outside off. Ben Duckett slaps it hardtowaards deep point. SIngle taken.
Default_Commentary: 18.3: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: Fuller and pitching it down the leg, shaping it more inward, urging the batter to perform a miss time flick. Ollie Pope goes for the clip but misses the connection.
Default_Commentary: 18.4: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Length delivery on middle. Ollie Pope tucks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Default_Commentary: 18.5: Vishwa Fernando to Ollie Pope, 1 run.

Commentary: FOUR! That one traveled like a bullet! Hard-length delivery, angling it away from the left-hander, away from the off stump. Ben Duckett frees his arms and punches it hard through the cover region for four more runs.
Default_Commentary: 18.6: Vishwa Fernando to Ben Duckett, Four!

Commentary: Full and just outside off, shaping it away from the stumps. Ollie Pope shoulder arms the delivery.
Default_Commentary: 19.1: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: On a length, pitching it just outside off and again nipping it away. Ollie Pope hangs back and eases it towards off side.
Default_Commentary: 19.2: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Pitched up, on middle. Ollie Pope lunges and blocks it towards mid on.
Default_Commentary: 19.3: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Full and outside off, on the fifth stump, swinging it out. Ollie Pope is happy make another leave.
Default_Commentary: 19.4: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: Pitches it up, outside off, nipping it away. Ollie Pope prods and taps it towards cover.
Default_Commentary: 19.5: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! This is a massive wicket for Sri Lanka! Lahiru Kumara gets the big fish and the bowling change works for Lanka. He bangs this one short and on middle and leg, Joe Root goes for the pull, but this one gets a bit big on him. It goes off the top edge towards fine leg, Vishwa Fernando there struggles to settle under it, but judges it well, in the end, to take a fantastic catch moving backwards. Root knew the moment he hit that and started to walk back. A rare failure for him as he departs on 13, and England lose their third now! Lahiru Kumara, though expensive gets his second wicket and breaks the 51-run stand between Root and Pope.
Default_Commentary: 38.3: Lahiru Kumara to Joe Root, OUT! c Vishwa Fernando b Lahiru Kumara.
Howout: c Vishwa Fernando b Lahiru Kumara

Commentary: Massive appeal for caught behind, but turned down! The keeper convinces his skipper, DDS to take the review. Asitha Fernando bangs this hard into the pitch, on middle, angling in, Ollie Pope comes down the track to hook it away, but misses and it goes very close from his gloves, Dinesh Chandimal dives to his left to grab it one-handed. However, UltraEdge shows no spike and Sri Lanka lose a review here.
Default_Commentary: 41.5: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, No run.

He moves to 97 now!

Commentary: FOUR! HUNDRED FOR POPE! 7th Test century for him and his first at the Oval, his home ground! Asitha Fernando serves this full again, outside off, Ollie Pope extends his arms and smashes it through cover-point for a boundary. This has been a really fantastic knock from Pope, and he becomes the first player to score his first seven Test hundreds against seven different oppositions. Pope becomes the second fastest English skipper to score a hundred, just behind one of the greats of English cricket, Graham Gooch, who achieved this feat in just 95 deliveries way back in 1990 against India, at Lord's.
Default_Commentary: 43.5: Asitha Fernando to Ollie Pope, Four!

Commentary: No run.

Commentary: Kumara starts from over the stumps, and lands it on the money, around off and nipping back into the batter. Harry Brook hops on the back foot to punch it to the off side and gets a thick leading edge towards wide gully where Pathum Nissanka dives to his right and intercepts the ball.

Commentary: An appeal for caught behind and the finger goes up! The umpire raises his finger but Harry Brook thinks otherwise and goes upstairs straightaway signaling the 'T' to review! Lahiru Kumara hurls it fuller in length and well outside off, with slight away deviation after pitching. Harry Brook extends his arms to play the expansive cover drive but gets beaten and Dinesh Chandimal takes a regulation take behind the pegs. UltraEdge however, confirms that ball just about flies past the outside edge without any murmur. Harry Brook survives, courtesy to a sharp review. Sri Lankans are absolutely distraught as they believe there was some noise off the willow.

Commentary: DROPPED! Dear, oh dear! Asitha Fernando has put down an absolute sitter! Just about sums up Sri Lanka's condition in this series. That should have been taken! Milan Rathnayake bowls full and moves a bit away from the batter from outside off, Harry Brook shows intent and skips down the track to loft it over the cover-point but tries to hit it too hard and loses his shape. Hence, slices it off the toe end of the bat in the air and towards deep point. Asitha Fernando has all the time in the world to settle underneath the ball, but slips while doing so and grasses this easy grab. Harry Brook survives for the second time in just a span of a couple of overs.

Commentary: A huge confident appeal for LBW from Milan Rathnayake and Dinesh Chandimal but 'No' says the umpire, Joel Wilson! Sri Lankan skipper, Dhananjaya de Silva opines that height might be the factor and denies to take the review. Milan Rathnayake bowls it full and holds the off stump line, Ollie Pope gets in a bit of a tangle as he pats his front foot and looks to defend it, but plays over the line of the ball. It passes very close to the inside edge, and clips on his knee role and carries through to the keeper. Good call from DDS to not go upstairs as the ball was clipping the off stump on the umpire's call.

A lot of balls have gone there, but Lanka have been stubborn with the slip placements.

Commentary: OUT! BRILLIANTLY TAKEN! Milan Rathnayake gets another important breakthrough for Sri Lanka. Harry Brook looked a bit uncomfortable in this session, and the pressure has got to him. This one is fuller in length and just outside off, tempter, Harry Brook cannot stop himself from going after it, but he fails to get his drive down along the ground and ends up airing it flat and hard, Kamindu Mendis at short covers flies to his right and takes a fantastic catch. Brook departs for 19 and Milan Rathnayake breaks the 70-run stand between Pope and Brook.
Default_Commentary: 52.4: Milan Rathnayake to Harry Brook, OUT! c Kamindu Mendis b Milan Rathnayake.

Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR AND TAKEN! Sri Lankan skipper, DDS strikes now and England have now lost three quick wickets with the tail exposed. Dhananjaya de Silva loops it up, providing a few more revolutions on it, drops it full and on the leg stump line from around the stumps, Gus Atkinson gets lured in the flight and skips down the track to heave it over the deep mid-wicket region. He is a bit early in the shot and swings through, but gets no real timing on it. The bat twists in his hands and the ball travels off the splice of the bat behind mid-wicket. Milan Rathnayake runs forward a few yards from deep mid-wicket, settles underneath it and takes it comfortably. Gus Atkinson, the centurion from the second Test couldn't bat through for long this time around.

Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR AND TAKEN AGAIN! This time, it's the English skipper, Ollie Pope who tried to take the aggressive route but holes out. Sri Lanka, right back in the game now. Vishwa Fernando bangs it short and on the line of the middle and leg stump. Pope moves on the back foot and gets underneath it. Swings hard into the leg side, flat in the air and straight to the man at deep backward square. Dimuth Karunaratne makes no mistake and takes a brilliant catch at deep square leg. Ollie Pope just cannot believe what he has done and England now slip from a comfy 290/4 to 307/8. A huge round of applause for Pope though as he departs on a well-crafted 154 off 156 deliveries.

Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR AND TAKEN! A momentous collapse for England and Sri Lanka have managed to sneak back in the contest after a dismal outing on the first day. Milan Rathnayake bowls it on the back of a length, around off, it springs off the deck a bit and comes high on the batter. Shoaib Bashir clears his front leg and tries to play a wild heave across the line, but as the ball gets heavier on him, he ends up slicing it off the high end of the bat. The ball airs in the overcast skies, and swirls over the cover region. Lahiru Kumara there stationed at the covers takes the simplest of the catches. England have lost 6 wickets in the last 35 runs, and more importantly within the last 10 overs.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND GONE! That is why Chris Woakes is so important for this England team. He answers back in his own style and sends Kusal Mendis back to the hut. This one lands on a good length in that channel outside off, nips away slightly, Mendis gets drawn forward trying to push at it, but gets a thick outside edge towards the second slip where Harry Brook takes a sharp catch. Mendis' brief stay comes to an end! Sri Lanka are 70/2.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! What a special moment for Josh Hull. First Test wicket for him and he is all pumped up! Josh Hull pitches this one up, on a very fuller length, outside off, and invites Pathum Nissanka to attempt the drive again. Nissanka gets a bit greedy and tries to cash on the width offered. But, the ball is too full to perform the drive. Nissanka though, goes through his shot. His bat twists in his hand and the ball travels off from the high end of the willow, and as a result, it goes flat in the air, just above the grass towards short cover. Chris Woakes stationed at the mentioned position throws himself to the direction of the ball, dives low to his right and takes a fabulous catch, inches above the grass. Pathum Nissanka the only Sri Lankan batter who looked confident walks back now on a quick 64. Sri Lanka are in a huge trouble as they slip to 91/4.
Default_Commentary: 15.3: Josh Hull to Pathum Nissanka, OUT! c Chris Woakes b Josh Hull.
Howout: c Chris Woakes b Josh Hull

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Redemption for Josh Hull! He dropped DDS on Day 2, but now sends him back to the hut. This is actually a well-directed bouncer from the youngster, on middle, Dhananjaya de Silva goes for the hook shot, but fails to transfer the weight fully on the back foot and the ball gets big on him as well. As a result, he gets a top edge that flies towards fine leg, Shoaib Bashir stationed there as the trap, settles under it nicely and takes a good catch. The Sri Lankan skipper goes back after a well-made 69! Sri Lanka are 220/6.
Default_Commentary: 47.5: Josh Hull to Dhananjaya de Silva, OUT! c Shoaib Bashir b Josh Hull.
Howout: c Shoaib Bashir b Josh Hull

Commentary: Back of a length and around off, Milan Rathnayake punches it through covers for a single.
Default_Commentary: 47.6: Josh Hull to Milan Rathnayake, 1 run.

Commentary: Short of a length and on leg, Milan Rathnayake gets cramped up trying to work it away and misses, it goes off his thigh pads towards square leg. A leg bye is taken.
Default_Commentary: 48.1: Chris Woakes to Milan Rathnayake, Leg bye.

Commentary: Pitches it up, on off, Kamindu Mendis blocks it down the pitch.
Default_Commentary: 48.2: Chris Woakes to Kamindu Mendis, No run.

Commentary: Full again and on middle and off, Kamindu Mendis knocks it away towards mid off for a run.
Default_Commentary: 48.3: Chris Woakes to Kamindu Mendis, 1 run.

Commentary: BEAUTY! Chris Woakes serves this full again and just on off, swings away sharply, Milan Rathnayake goes fishing at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 48.4: Chris Woakes to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: On a length and on middle, Milan Rathnayake stays back and keeps it out to the off side.
Default_Commentary: 48.5: Chris Woakes to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: Another great outswinger! Over pitched and around off, shaping away a long way again, Milan Rathnayake tries to play at it but misses, the ball zips past the outside edge again.
Default_Commentary: 48.6: Chris Woakes to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length and on off, Mendis stands tall and defends it to the leg side.
Default_Commentary: 49.1: Josh Hull to Kamindu Mendis, No run.

Commentary: Just short of leg slip! The fielder there is strategically stationed! Hull bowls the length ball and angles it on the pads, Kamindu Mendis hops on the back foot and looks to glance it to the leg side but due to a bit of an extra bounce, the ball lobs off from his bat's inner half and falls just ahead of leg slip.
Default_Commentary: 49.2: Josh Hull to Kamindu Mendis, No run.

Commentary: FIVE WIDES! Oh, dear! Hull bangs in a bumper angling into the body of Mendis. It flies over the batter's head and over Smith behind the pegs who has no chance of collecting that one. It races away to the deep fine leg fence.
Default_Commentary: 49.3: Josh Hull to Kamindu Mendis, 5 Wides!

Commentary: EDGED AND FOUR! Some away movement around off, pitching up, Kamindu Mendis gets lured on the width and goes for a cover drive off the front foot. Ends up getting a thick outside edge that flies past the vacant gully region for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 49.3: Josh Hull to Kamindu Mendis, Four!

Commentary: Pitched up again outside off, Mendis drives it crisply but finds Pope at the covers.
Default_Commentary: 49.4: Josh Hull to Kamindu Mendis, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length and around off, Kamindu Mendis defends and gets an inside edge on his back leg.
Default_Commentary: 49.5: Josh Hull to Kamindu Mendis, No run.

Commentary: Good length outside off, shaping away, this is worked to the right of cover for one by Kamindu Mendis.
Default_Commentary: 49.6: Josh Hull to Kamindu Mendis, 1 run.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN AT FIRST SLIP! An absolute seed from Woakes to dismiss the well-settled Kamindu Mendis! Chris Woakes stays over the stumps and pitches it fractionally on the good length, around off, and also gets a considerable movement. The ball curves away from the southpaw as Kamindu Mendis opens up his body and hangs his bat away from him. Gets a thick outside edge that carries straight towards Joe Root, one of the safest fielders at slips. Root gobbles it up nicely. Sri Lanka have now lost both of their well-settled batters in the first hour of Day 3. They trail by 92 runs now.
Default_Commentary: 50.1: Chris Woakes to Kamindu Mendis, OUT! c Joe Root b Chris Woakes.
Howout: c Joe Root b Chris Woakes

Commentary: An away swinger outside off, Fernando leaves it alone to the keeper.
Default_Commentary: 50.2: Chris Woakes to Vishwa Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Genuine movement, outside off and curving away from the good length, Vishwa Fernando lets it be.
Default_Commentary: 50.3: Chris Woakes to Vishwa Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Peach! Woakes brings the angle a bit more closer and gets the ball to leave the right hander from around off, Vishwa Fernando is square up and gets beaten all ends up.
Default_Commentary: 50.4: Chris Woakes to Vishwa Fernando, No run.

Commentary: FOUR BYES! Pitched up, full but sliding down the leg stump line. It wildly swings further down leg after pitching and Jamie Smith has no chance to collect it behind the pegs. Runs away to the deep fine fence.
Default_Commentary: 50.5: Chris Woakes to Vishwa Fernando, 4 Byes.

Commentary: Nasty bumper that! On the bodyline, but Vishwa Fernando just about manages to fend it away.
Default_Commentary: 50.6: Chris Woakes to Vishwa Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Hull bowls it very full, on a tight line, at the middle and gets a good away swing, Milan Rathnayake negotiates it well and jabs it to wide of mid on for a single.
Default_Commentary: 51.1: Josh Hull to Milan Rathnayake, 1 run.

Commentary: Short-pitched delivery angling on the middle and leg, Vishwa Fernando rides on the bounce and drops it near the strip with soft hands.
Default_Commentary: 51.2: Josh Hull to Vishwa Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Holds his line, but varies his length, on that in-between length, Vishwa Fernando tucks it to the square leg region.
Default_Commentary: 51.3: Josh Hull to Vishwa Fernando, No run.

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Josh Hull gets his third wicket! However, Vishwa Fernando has decided to challenge the on-field decision and goes upstairs to review it. Looks pretty straight and plumb though. Josh Hull bowls it on the good length and lets the ball curve into the batter, starts from the middle and off channel, and moves into the leg stump line, Vishwa Fernando pats his front foot and looks to defend it but plays over the line of the ball as he doesn't expect the ball to tail in that much, and gets rapped straight on the pad. UltraEdge shows no murmur and the Ball Tracker confirms three reds.
Default_Commentary: 51.4: Josh Hull to Vishwa Fernando, OUT! lbw b Josh Hull.
Howout: lbw b Josh Hull

Commentary: Holds onto his line, around off with a gentle outswing, Lahiru Kumara gets behind the line and taps it to the off side.
Default_Commentary: 51.5: Josh Hull to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Good length on off stump, with a bit of an extra bounce. Lahiru Kumara fends from his crease, and gets a thick inside edge that runs down to backward square leg.
Default_Commentary: 51.6: Josh Hull to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Full and shaping away outside off, Rathnayake leaves it alone to the keeper.
Default_Commentary: 52.1: Chris Woakes to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: Full and well outside off, Rathnayake shoulders his arms to this one.
Default_Commentary: 52.2: Chris Woakes to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: Drags his length and hits the hard length on the stumps, Rathnayake defends it off the backfoot to the left of the bowler.
Default_Commentary: 52.3: Chris Woakes to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: Gets that lateral movement does Chris Woakes this time! Length ball that leaves the left hander after pitching, outside off, Milan Rathnayake lets it pass.
Default_Commentary: 52.4: Chris Woakes to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: This time Woakes swings it into the batter. On the back of a length, and shaping in, on middle, Milan Rathnayake is cramped up for room and gets pinged on the gloves.
Default_Commentary: 52.5: Chris Woakes to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: Excellent stop that by Pope at gully! Length outside off, at a gentle pace, Rathnayake cuts it very late. It almost comes off the outside edge and Pope at gully stops it with a dive.
Default_Commentary: 52.6: Chris Woakes to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: A steep bumper at the pegs, Lahiru Kumara ducks underneath it.
Default_Commentary: 53.1: Josh Hull to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Slight away movement, outside off on a good length, Lahiru Kumara does not poke at it and leaves.
Default_Commentary: 53.2: Josh Hull to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: That questioning length now! Swings it away, but this time, the length is fuller and closer to the off peg, but still outside off, Lahiru Kumara goes for a front foot defence but plays inside the line of the ball, and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 53.3: Josh Hull to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: That in-between length, angling on the pads, Lahiru Kumara is a bit late as he tries to tuck it away to the leg side but gets pinged on the thigh pad.
Default_Commentary: 53.4: Josh Hull to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: DROPPED! Olly Stone, what have you done? Josh Hull slips in a low full toss on the stumps, Lahiru Kumara does not really get his bat underneath it properly and goes through the aerial flick. The ball flies off the bottom end of the bat towards the deep fine region where Olly Stone runs in a few yards from deep fine, gets in a bit of an indecision as he first tries to pouch it with a regulation under cup, but then tries to grab it with a reverse cup and shells it in the end. They cross.
Default_Commentary: 53.5: Josh Hull to Lahiru Kumara, 1 run.

Commentary: FOUR! Salt on the wounds! Hull bowls it a bit short outside off, Rathnayake gets on top of the bounce and guides it nicely through the vacant point region for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 53.6: Josh Hull to Milan Rathnayake, Four!

Commentary: Length delivery on the stumps, Kumara hangs back and blocks it to mid on.
Default_Commentary: 54.1: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Good length on middle, Kumara defends it straight back to Stone.
Default_Commentary: 54.2: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Edged but just short of the fourth slip! A bit of an extra bounce on a length, over the top of off, Lahiru Kumara fends it off the outer half of the bat, and the ball lands just ahead of Ollie Pope at the fourth slip who collects it on a bounce.
Default_Commentary: 54.3: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Banged in short outside off, Kumara drops his wrists and lets it go behind.
Default_Commentary: 54.4: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Bowls it closer to the body, on the middle and on a good length, Lahiru Kumara gets behind the line and bunts it to the pitch.
Default_Commentary: 54.5: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Aims the off peg, on a length, Lahiru Kumara prods ahead and defends it to the short cover. A maiden over to start with for Ollie Stone.
Default_Commentary: 54.6: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Hits the deck hard, on off, Milan Rathnayake punches it off the back foot to the short cover region.
Default_Commentary: 55.1: Josh Hull to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: FOUR BYES! That takes off from the surface prodigiously, on the middle, Milan Rathnayake tries the ramp shot but it is still too high to execute that shot. The ball flies over the leaping Jamie Smith behind the wickets and bullets down to the fence behind him.
Default_Commentary: 55.2: Josh Hull to Milan Rathnayake, 4 Byes.

Commentary: Sticks to the short ball plan does Josh Hull. Outside off, Milan Rathnayake mistimes his cut towards deep point for a single.
Default_Commentary: 55.3: Josh Hull to Milan Rathnayake, 1 run.

Commentary: Hull goes way too full in search of that swing. Gets a good seam movement away from the batter, outside off, Lahiru Kumara brings his bat to poke at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 55.4: Josh Hull to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Nice and full, curving away after landing, Lahiru Kumara sees closely and lets it go.
Default_Commentary: 55.5: Josh Hull to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Spears in a full toss on the middle, Lahiru Kumara firmly pushes it to mid on.
Default_Commentary: 55.6: Josh Hull to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Stone continues, and pitches it on a fullish length, at off, Milan Rathnayake pats his front foot in the line but gets it off the inner half of the willow towards short mid-wicket.
Default_Commentary: 56.1: Olly Stone to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: Swing and a miss! Length-delivery outside off, Milan Rathnayake looks to loft it over the inner ring but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 56.2: Olly Stone to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: There's that sharp bouncer again! Stone cramps Rathnayake with a well-directed bumper on the middle and leg, Milan Rathnayake has no time to react and wears it on the body as he tries to get away from the line.
Default_Commentary: 56.3: Olly Stone to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: Ohh! An extra bit of bounce again! Not that short from Stone, at off on a fractionally fuller length, which takes off from the surface. Milan Rathnayake is taken by surprise by the bounce and fends it off the gloves in front of the slips.
Default_Commentary: 56.4: Olly Stone to Milan Rathnayake, No run.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Olly Stone too, gets his third wicket and Sri Lanka are 9 down now. Olly Stone follows up the short balls with a tempting good-length delivery outside off, it again springs off a bit and gets heavy on the batter to negotiate. Milan Rathnayake opts for a back foot square cut but swings under it getting a thick outside edge. Jamie Smith does the rest by taking a regulation catch behind the wickets. Sri Lanka staring down the barrel at the moment and trails by 77 runs.
Default_Commentary: 56.5: Olly Stone to Milan Rathnayake, OUT! c Jamie Smith b Olly Stone.
Howout: c Jamie Smith b Olly Stone

Commentary: Wow! This is some really nice bowling from Stone! Pitches it on the middle and gets a good nip away from the deck, on a length, Asitha Fernando sways away from the line of the ball and tries to slash it with a horizontal bat. Misses the outside edge by a margin.
Default_Commentary: 56.6: Olly Stone to Asitha Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Bashir with a slip and a short leg in place, comes from around the pegs. Too slow, looped up outside off and spinning away, Lahiru Kumara slashes it though point for a single.
Default_Commentary: 57.1: Shoaib Bashir to Lahiru Kumara, 1 run.

Commentary: Over the stumps now with a slip and leg slip in place. Full, turning in on middle and leg, tickled to the square leg region.
Default_Commentary: 57.2: Shoaib Bashir to Asitha Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Slower through the air, full and on leg, Asitha Fernando goes for a sweep but misses and gets pinged on the pads.
Default_Commentary: 57.3: Shoaib Bashir to Asitha Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Nicely tossed up on the fuller length outside off, Fernando goes for a drive but misses.
Default_Commentary: 57.4: Shoaib Bashir to Asitha Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Slips it down leg on a fuller length, it lands right on the rough and turns sharply down leg, Asitha Fernando leaves.
Default_Commentary: 57.5: Shoaib Bashir to Asitha Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Sharp turn, on the stumps, Asitha looks to slog this but inside edges to the thigh pad.
Default_Commentary: 57.6: Shoaib Bashir to Asitha Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Stone charges in from over the stumps, lands it on a good length, slightly outside off, Lahiru Kumara covers his line, checks the ball and decides to leave it.
Default_Commentary: 58.1: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: On middle, on a length, Lahiru Kumara tries to pull it into the stands but gets no real timing at it. Hits it flat and off the toe end to the bowler.
Default_Commentary: 58.2: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Full, and angling away from the southpaw, Lahiru Kumara stays deep inside the crease and looks to work it through covers but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 58.3: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: 250 up for Sri Lanka! That in-between length, on middle, Lahiru Kumara attempts to clobber it away with the pull shot but mistimes it to wide of mid-wicket for a single. They trail by 75 more runs now with just a solitary wicket in hand.
Default_Commentary: 58.4: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, 1 run.

Commentary: Good bowling! Length-delivery over the top of middle, Asitha Fernando walks away from the line of the ball and brings his bat horizontally to slash but gets beaten.
Default_Commentary: 58.5: Olly Stone to Asitha Fernando, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Wow, that's a good shot! Olly Stone varies his length and bowls it quite fuller this time, on the stumps, Asitha Fernando skips down the track, creates room for him and slaps it over the bowler's head for a boundary to wide long off.
Default_Commentary: 58.6: Olly Stone to Asitha Fernando, Four!

Commentary: Bashir tosses it up, gets that in-drift to the pads, Lahiru Kumara looks to clear the fence with a swipe across the line but wears on the pads.
Default_Commentary: 59.1: Shoaib Bashir to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Very slow, on a length, on middle, Lahiru Kumara works it off the back foot to mid-wicket.
Default_Commentary: 59.2: Shoaib Bashir to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Looped up, outside off, on a good length, Lahiru Kumara cuts it to Brook at backward point. Brook dives to his left and parries the ball to the cover region. Allows a single.
Default_Commentary: 59.3: Shoaib Bashir to Lahiru Kumara, 1 run.

Commentary: Sharp turn from over the pegs, full and on middle, Asitha Fernando sits down to reverse sweep but wears on the pads.
Default_Commentary: 59.4: Shoaib Bashir to Asitha Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Too full, on the stumps, Asitha Fernando again employs the reverse sweep but inside edges onto the pitch.
Default_Commentary: 59.5: Shoaib Bashir to Asitha Fernando, No run.

Commentary: Slower through the air, on the fullish length, on middle, Asitha Fernando charges down to the pitch and lofts it over the inner ring. Ben Duckett from mid-wicket chases down to the deep as the ball loses steam on the dampened outfield. Picks the ball before the ropes and the batters take a couple of runs.
Default_Commentary: 59.6: Shoaib Bashir to Asitha Fernando, 2 runs.

Commentary: Olly Stone bangs it into the surface around off, Lahiru Kumara fends it a bit uppishly off the back foot but the ball lands just ahead of Ollie Pope stationed at gully. Pope crouches and stops the ball. Oh, wait! The on-field umpires converge and discuss to check it for a fair catch. After examining several angles, it is deemed that the ball landed just before Pope's fingers. NOT OUT appears on the giant screen.
Default_Commentary: 60.1: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length, outside off, Lahiru Kumara is happy to let it be.
Default_Commentary: 60.2: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Outside leg, on a length, Lahiru Kumara swings hard at it for a pull but gets it off the higher part of the bat towards the square leg region for a single.
Default_Commentary: 60.3: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, 1 run.

Commentary: Follows the batter does Stone, On a length angling outside leg, Asitha Fernando walks away from the line and pats it to wide cover and sets off for a quick single. The cover fielder moves to his left, and is quick to pick and throw in one action to the non-striker's end. Has a shy and Asitha Fernando running with his afterburners gets home just about safely to complete the single.
Default_Commentary: 60.4: Olly Stone to Asitha Fernando, 1 run.

Commentary: An appeal for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved! Short and on a very tight line on the back of a length, on middle and leg, Lahiru Kumara tries to move away from the line and goes for a pull shot. However, the ball is too close to execute that shot and just passes from next to gloves to the keeper. Jamie Smith catches it safely behind the wickets. Pope wants to have a check at it and goes upstairs but UltraEdge confirms that there's no scratch. England burn a review here.
Default_Commentary: 60.5: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: Stone again tests the batter's patience with a sharp bouncer on the stumps, Kumara makes room and looks to upper cut it but misses.
Default_Commentary: 60.6: Olly Stone to Lahiru Kumara, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Good shot! Shoaib Bashir pushes it through, full and on the off stump line, Asitha Fernando finds the length into his arc and sits down on his knees. Connects well and slogs it over deep mid-wicket for a six.
Default_Commentary: 61.1: Shoaib Bashir to Asitha Fernando, Four!

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Shoaib Bashir does the job of picking the final wicket, and his first. But hang on, this is reviewed straightaway by Asitha as he thinks it came off his forearm and not the glove or the bat. Shoaib Bashir pushes it through again, lands full and outside off, with a hint of a turn into the batter. Asitha Fernando premeditates the reverse sweep but misses. The ball lobs off Fernando's shoulder Jamie Smith is quick to react, moves forward and takes a good sharp catch. However, UltraEdge comes up and it confirms that the ball did brush faintly on Asitha's gloves, which means it is out and Sri Lanka are all out on 263.
Default_Commentary: 61.2: Shoaib Bashir to Asitha Fernando, OUT! c Jamie Smith b Shoaib Bashir.
Howout: c Jamie Smith b Shoaib Bashir

Commentary: Ben Duckett and England are underway straightaway! Asitha Fernando starts with a back-of-a-length delivery, just outside off, Ben Duckett gets on his toes and punches it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Default_Commentary: 0.1: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, 2 runs.

Commentary: Goes fuller this time, on off, Ben Duckett taps it in front of mid off and takes a quick single.
Default_Commentary: 0.2: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, 1 run.

Commentary: Shows intent! Asitha Fernando lands this on a hard length and on off, angles in sharply, Dan Lawrence uses his feet to cut the swing but gets beaten by the bounce, it goes off his hips towards fine leg. A leg bye is taken.
Default_Commentary: 0.3: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, Leg bye.

Commentary: Pitched up but swinging down the leg side, Ben Duckett tries to flick it away but misses.
Default_Commentary: 0.4: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length and around middle, Ben Duckett stays back and blocks it out.
Default_Commentary: 0.5: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Hits the length hard, on off, Ben Duckett pats it down towards mid off. 4 runs off the first over!
Default_Commentary: 0.6: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: Milan Rathnayake begins with a full delivery, on off, Dan Lawrence gets his front foot closer to the line of the ball and knocks it towards mid on.
Default_Commentary: 1.1: Milan Rathnayake to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Wayward! Milan Rathnayake loses his line and serves this full, but way down the leg side, Dan Lawrence looks to glance it away but is nowhere near the ball.
Default_Commentary: 1.2: Milan Rathnayake to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Full and straight in line with the stumps, not much movement, Dan Lawrence drills it away straight to mid on.
Default_Commentary: 1.3: Milan Rathnayake to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! Further evidence of how Dan Lawrence is going to play! Milan Rathnayake lands this back of a length and outside off, shapes away a bit, Dan Lawrence advances down the track, makes some room and carves it away over extra covers for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 1.4: Milan Rathnayake to Dan Lawrence, Four!

Commentary: Nicely played! On a length and on middle, Dan Lawrence tucks it away with nice timing, deep square leg runs to his right to pick it up, but the batters take three by then.
Default_Commentary: 1.5: Milan Rathnayake to Dan Lawrence, 3 runs.

Commentary: FOUR! Ben Duckett joins the party now! Milan Rathnayake tries to test the batter with a short one, on middle, but this one sits up nicely for the batter, Ben Duckett gets on top of it and pulls it away over mid-wicket for a boundary. 11 runs off the over then!
Default_Commentary: 1.6: Milan Rathnayake to Ben Duckett, Four!

Commentary: BEAUTY! Asitha Fernando hits the length hard and in that channel outside off, gets it to shape away nicely, this one takes off as well, Dan Lawrence stays in his crease and has a poke at it, but just gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 2.1: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Uppish but safe! Fuller this time and around off, shaping away again, Dan Lawrence steps across to flick it away but closes the bat face early, gets a leading edge that luckily for him goes through the vacant backward point region for a brace.
Default_Commentary: 2.2: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, 2 runs.

Commentary: Pitches it up, on off, nips away again, Dan Lawrence looks to drive but gets an outside edge this time that goes along the ground wide of third man. Two runs takens.
Default_Commentary: 2.3: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, 2 runs.

Commentary: Dan Lawrence is not going to die wondering here! Good length and around middle, angling in, Dan Lawrence uses his feet and has a wild hoick across the line, gets an inside edge through square leg for just one.
Default_Commentary: 2.4: Asitha Fernando to Dan Lawrence, 1 run.

Commentary: On a length and on middle, Ben Duckett pats it down to the leg side.
Default_Commentary: 2.5: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, No run.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Asitha Fernando draws first blood! A soft dismissal but Sri Lanka won't mind one bit. This one is full and swings into middle and leg, Ben Duckett stays deep in his crease and tries to loft it away across the line, but fails to get underneath the ball and his bat twists in his hand as well. As a result, he ends up lobbing it straight towards mid on where Vishwa Fernando takes a dolly. A shake of the head from Duckett, and England loses their first. Still leads by 82!
Default_Commentary: 2.6: Asitha Fernando to Ben Duckett, OUT! c Vishwa Fernando b Asitha Fernando.
Howout: c Vishwa Fernando b Asitha Fernando

Commentary: On a length and on off, shaping away, Dan Lawrence stabs it out towards short covers.
Default_Commentary: 3.1: Milan Rathnayake to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Back of a length but angling down the leg side, Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
Default_Commentary: 3.2: Milan Rathnayake to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Goes fuller and around off, swinging away, Dan Lawrence takes no chances and lets it go.
Default_Commentary: 3.3: Milan Rathnayake to Dan Lawrence, No run.

Commentary: Pulls his length back a bit, on off, Dan Lawrence pats it towards mid-wicket for a single.

Commentary: OUT! DRAGGED ON! The change in bowling has worked for Sri Lanka and England lose their skipper right on the stroke of Lunch. Ollie Pope walks back to the dressing room in distraught and is absolutely livid with himself! Lahiru Kumara steams in from over the stumps and hurls it on the back of a length, just outside off, and it nips back into the batter after pitching. Ollie Pope hops on the back foot and attempts to run it down to the short third region, an area where he was so productive in the first innings. But it is too close to play that shot and Pope ends up inside edging it into the sticks. Lahiru Kumara sprints in celebration and that will be LUNCH on DAY 3.
Default_Commentary: 7.4: Lahiru Kumara to Ollie Pope, OUT! b Lahiru Kumara.
Howout: b Lahiru Kumara

Two taken.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Lahiru Kumara strikes again. He gets his second wicket and gives a sendoff to Lawrence who falls for his own aggression! Lahiru Kumara continues from 'over the stumps and lands it on that in-between length, aiming the stumps, Dan Lawrence throws himself for a big shot into the stands over the off side. Gets his dancing shoes on, swings hard but loses his shape in the process and ends up outside edging it straight to Dinesh Chandimal behind the wickets. Chandimal makes no mistake and England lose their third wicket on 56. Sri Lanka fighting back hard here. Dan Lawrence departs on a run-a-ball 35.

Commentary: FOUR! Classy shot! Vishwa Fernando serves this very full and just around off, Joe Root leans on to his drive nicely, keeps his head right over the ball and creams it through covers for a boundary. Root surpasses Kumar Sangakkara's tally of Test runs.

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Joe Root is gone! Massive moment in this Test! Absolute corker of a delivery from Vishwa Fernando and the bowling change works again for Sri Lanka. Dhananjaya de Silva is absolutely spot on with his decisions here. Fernando steams in from over the wicket and nails the yorker with precision, on middle, swinging in very late, Joe Root gets surprised by it and looks to clip it away, but his head falls and he gets hit on the front pad on the full. A huge shout for LBW, and up goes the finger. Root reviews it but he does not look that confident. UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved and Ball Tracking shows that the ball is pitching the line of the stumps and crashing into the middle and leg stumps on the projection. Root walks back for just 12! England slips from 56/2 to 66/4. Sri Lanka right back into the contest.
Default_Commentary: 14.3: Vishwa Fernando to Joe Root, OUT! lbw b Vishwa Fernando.
Howout: lbw b Vishwa Fernando

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Vishwa Fernando with the double whammy! He is absolutely on fire here! England are crumbling at the Oval, who would have thought this? This is another sharp in-swinger, full and and on middle from over the wicket, once again swings in late, Harry Brook gets stuck in his crease and looks to flick it away, but misses it completely and gets rapped on the pads. Fernando already starts running away as an appeal goes up, and the finger goes up as well. Brook takes a review, but the only thing that can save him here is if he has hit that. Otherwise, it's plumb. UltraEdge shows no bat and Ball Tracking comes up with three reds. England lose half their side now and another review as well!

Howout: lbw b Vishwa Fernando

Lahiru Kumara goes wide of the crease and hits the good length, on off, this one angles in and then shapes away a bit, Chris Woakes stays in his crease and looks to defend it away from his body, gets a thin outside edge behind where Dinesh Chandimal dives forward and takes a good catch. England six down now!

Vishwa Fernando hits the good length and pitches it on the leg stump line, Gus Atkinson misses to connect, and the ball hits the pads, and rolls towards wide of square leg. The square leg fielder charges at the ball with Atkinson stranded in the middle of the pitch to complete the run. A direct hit and Atkinson was a goner. But wait, hang on, Dhananjaya de Silva decides to opt a review for LBW here. Well, a waste of time as the Ball Tracking shows it is clearly pitching outside leg.

Commentary: FOUR! Pathum Nissanka fittingly hits the winning runs! SRI LANKA WIN BY 8 WICKETS! Shoaib Bashir drags his length back, outside off, Pathum Nissanka lets it come to him and cuts it away nicely wide of backward point for a boundary. Angelo Mathews hugs Nissanka as they get appreciation from the crowd and the English players. We can also see the Lankan skipper, Dhananjaya de Silva shaking hands with the head coach of England, Brendon McCullum. A famous victory and this will surely go down as one of the finest moments in Sri Lanka's history.
